page.title: 02BIRDS ON KELSEY HEAD
page.content: First we saw a flock of{Pigeons,}in the flock was a black and white Pigeon. Next we saw a{Kestrel}hovering above us. We saw a{Skylark}on the path and followed it, but it kept on leading us away from it's nest. The next birds we saw were some{Starlings which rose from the pea field in a big flock. There were lots of Gulls about including{Black-Backed, Herring Gulls} and the{Fulmars}which keep their wings stiff in flight and rarely 'flap'. The Gulls' nesting sites were on little ledges in the cliff face. At the top of the cliff, in the earth just below grass level, there were holes made by {Swallows, Swifts}and{Sand Martins} which were their nests. A{Raven}was perched on top of a pole as a{Carrion {Crow}flew over and we later spotted a {Magpie.}
